I'm not sure if this is something we would want to maintain in the long run. It might be more appropriate to configure this at the systems level.

For example, would NGINX be able to solve your use case? Here is how such a thing could be configured using the [rewrite module](http://nginx.org/en/docs/http/ngx_http_rewrite_module.html):

```nginx
server {
  listen 80 default_server;
  listen [::]:80 default_server ipv6only=on;

  location = /tensorboard {
    return 302 /tensorboard/;
  }

  location /tensorboard {
    rewrite ^/tensorboard(/.*)$ $1 break;
    proxy_http_version 1.1;
    proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:6006;
  }
}
```

